# CCVAA multi-agent OS (shared)

## Roles

| Role | Primary contact | Owns |
|------|-----------------|------|
| Product Manager | Human CEO | Scope, priorities, advice, product docs |
| Developer | PM (via handoff) | Feature branches, PRs, implementation |
| QA | PM (via handoff) | Pass 1 / Pass 2 / baseline when backlog **Verifier = `agent`**; admin mailbox login via `.env.local`; Preview bypass via `.env.local` |

CEO talks **only** to the **Product Manager**. Repo docs are the shared brain — not chat history. PM invokes Developer / QA; CEO does not brief those roles directly.

**Chat titles:** `Product Manager` · `Developer` · `QA` (fixed; rename on session start).

## Canonical docs

- `AGENTS.md` — OS overview
- `docs/product/FEATURES.md` — living feature inventory (PM maintains); changelog **descending by date**
- `docs/product/BACKLOG.md` — feature backlogs / work IDs `{feature-slug}-{NNNN}`
- `docs/protocols/` — communication, handoff, GIT_DEPLOY, QA_AUTH, PREVIEW_PROTECTION, **CEO**
- `docs/templates/` — backlog-item, handoff, QA report templates

## Environments (agent Dev/QA)

- Dev: http://localhost:3000/
- Preview: Vercel URL for the feature branch/PR (pre-merge; **Deployment Protection** — bypass via `.env.local`)
- Production: https://ccvaa-web.vercel.app/ (`main` — QA Pass 2)
- **Out of agent flow:** https://ccvaa.ca/ — CEO manual only (DNS/cache)

Default ship path: feature branch → QA Preview → merge → QA on `ccvaa-web.vercel.app`. Each item **main-safe on `main` alone** — `docs/protocols/GIT_DEPLOY.md`.

## Hard constraints

- Never commit secrets (`.env.local`, credentials, mailbox passwords, `VERCEL_AUTOMATION_BYPASS_SECRET`)
- Commit / push / merge only when CEO explicitly asks — **except:** (1) `agent-os-*` after CEO **`verified`** (PM ships same turn); (2) **self-evolve** feature-branch **commits** after CEO kickoff (merge still CEO-only)
- Prefer feature branches + PRs when **Verifier = `agent`**; **`ceo` / `n/a`** default **`direct-to-main`** (do not invent feature-branch for ordinary agent-os docs)
- Prefer small, focused changes; do not over-engineer
- Agents do not use `ccvaa.ca` for Dev/QA passes
- Next.js 16 differs from older Next — read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before novel APIs; use `proxy.ts` not deprecated `middleware.ts`
